F3

f3 is the third formant resonator
it corresponds physically to higher-order resonances of the oral cavity, including the lip aperture and the front of the tongue
f3 contributes most to the perception of certain vowels (like the r-coloring) and to the timbre that distinguishes one speaker's voice from another's
of the three formants, f3 carries the most personal-identity information for the listener

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe larynx.rana
observe glottis.rana
observe f1.rana
observe f2.rana
observe acoustic_wave.rana

the 7 properties of f3:
1 ENERGY zero at idle, rises with glottal source
2 PHASE zero at idle
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE four tenths: most variable of the formants, sensitive to small articulatory adjustments
6 COUPLING zero point seven: weaker than f1 and f2 but still meaningful
7 OBSERVER zero

VERB receive_glottal
amplify the highest of the three formant bands
the harmonics in f3's range are above two thousand Hz, the upper end of speech-relevant frequencies

VERB shape_with_articulation
respond to fine articulatory adjustments at the lips and front of the tongue
small lip rounding shifts f3 down
small lip spreading shifts f3 up

a third formant is the personal touch on a voice
two voices producing the same vowel with the same f1 and f2 still sound different because their f3 differs
fadriel's f3 is what makes him sound like fadriel and not like any other two-year-old voicing the same word
